  "body": "## Simple Summary\r\nAdd a flag to all external calls which results in the `extcodesize`/`returndatasize` check being dropped\r\n\r\n## Motivation\r\n\"there are plenty of contracts that only interact with a set of whitelisted or validated at constructor time contracts which are wasting a good amount of gas on these extcodesize checks that will never fail\"\r\n\\- @transmissions11\r\n\r\n## Specification\r\nAdd a kwarg like `omit_contract_check` to all external calls. It defaults to `False` (keeping the current behavior) Ex.\r\n```python\r\nexternal_contract: ExternalContract\r\n\r\n...\r\n\r\ndef my_func():\r\n  self.external_contract.foo(..., omit_contract_check=True)\r\n```\r\n\r\n## References\r\nAdd any references that this VIP might reference (other VIPs/issues, links to blog posts, etc.)\r\n\r\n## Copyright\r\nCopyright and related rights waived via [CC0](https://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/)\r\n",
